      "citation_id": "[CITATION_8]",
      "span_text": "Based on spikelet and grain morphology, Harlan and de Wet developed a simplified classification of traditional sorghum cultivars into five basic races: Bicolor (B), Caudatum (C), Durra (D), Guinea (G) and Kafir (K), and ten intermediate races (in all pair-wise combinations of basic races)."
